By Chimezie Godfrey The Director General,(DG), National Institute for Policy and Strategic Studies, (NIPSS), Kuru, Professor Ayo Omotayo has commended the Nigerian Army (NA) for her support to the institute, especially in areas of staffing and logistics. Professor Omotayo gave the commendation today Tuesday 31 May 2022, during a courtesy call on the Chief of Army Staff (COAS), Lieutenant General Faruk Yahaya at the Army Headquarters Abuja.  The DG stated that the NA has been dauntless in protecting lives and property of Nigerians in the face of the security challenges bedeviling the nation. He noted that the NA has been forthcoming in providing logistics support to facilitate the operations of the institute. He lauded the NA on the achievements so far recorded in the fight against terrorism and insurgency in the country, urging the troops not to relent until the adversaries are defeated.  In his response, the COAS Lieutenant General Faruk Yahaya congratulated the DG on his appointment and appreciated the institute for the qualitative human development of the Armyâ€™s future leaders. Gen Yahaya assured that the NA will continue to support the institute to promote national development. The COAS donated a utility vehicle to the institution in appreciation of her contribution to capacity development of NA officers.  Present at the visit were Principal Staff Officers of the Army Headquarters and Nigerian Army Resource Centre, Management and Directing Staff of the institute, amongst others.